Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C and put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil for the pasta. Halve the @aubergine{1} lengthways, cut into 2cm wide strips, then chop into 2cm cubes. Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1} into roughly ½cm pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, then remove the core from the @bell pepper{1} and cut into 1cm slices.

Spread the aubergine and pepper out on a lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle over some @oil{} and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @pepper{grind}. Pop on the top shelf of your oven. Roast until soft and a little crispy around the edges, about ~{20%minutes}.

> Spread aubergine and pepper evenly for best roasting.

Heat a glug of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the onion and cook, stirring, ~{3%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and cook for another ~{1%minute}. Add the @pork sausage meat{225%g} to your pan. Break it up with a #wooden spoon{} and cook until slightly browned, ~{5%minutes}. Then add the @white wine vinegar{2%tbsp} and cook until almost evaporated.

Pour the @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can} into your pan along with the @water{100%ml}. Season with @salt{pinch}, @pepper{grind} and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch}. Leave to simmer and thicken, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add the @penne pasta{144%g} to your pan of boiling water. Cook until 'al dente', about ~{6%minutes}.

> 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle.

When cooked, drain in a #colander{}, return to the pan off the heat and drizzle over a little @oil{} to stop it from sticking.

Once the aubergine and pepper are ready, remove from your oven and stir into the tomato sauce along with the @olives{15}. Stir the pasta into the caponata and serve in big #bowls{}. For a dairy free option enjoy now, if you fancy a little extra grate over the @?parmesan cheese{20%g}.

> We like to leave our olives whole for texture but chop them up if you'd like them to blend in, or leave out altogether if you're not a fan!